Class Edge<N extends Comparable<N>,E extends Comparable<E>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • hw5.Edge<N,E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Edge<N,E>>

    public class Edge<N extends Comparable<N>,E extends Comparable<E>>
extends Object
implements Comparable<Edge<N,E>>
    Edge represents an immutable connection between two Nodes in Graph. It starts from one node and points to another node. It includes a Node that represents the parent Node it starts from, a Node that represents the children Node it ends with and a String that represents the label of itself.

    Examples of Edge include "Edge:label" and so on.
